{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":6},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5},"Le sculture da Alesa","","2009","\u003Cspan>Elisa Chiara Portale, «Le sculture da Alesa», in \u003Ci>Alaisa-Halaesa. Scavi e ricerche (1970-2007)\u003C/i>, a c. di G. Scibona e G. Tigano (Messina: Sicania, 2009), 67–92\u003C/span>",[7,126],{"file":8,"uri":8,"title":9,"status":10,"editionAuthor":12,"type":13,"objectType":17,"material":21,"condition":3,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":46,"places":51,"geo":61,"provenance":53,"provenanceGeo":65,"country":68,"region":69,"settlement":53,"repository":70,"idno":74,"textLang":77,"tmNumber":81,"facsimile":82,"letterHeights":89,"publications":90,"zotero":99,"keywords":109,"html":119,"bibl":120},"ISic000768","Dedication by a sevir to Concordia",{"_":11},"edited",null,{"_":14,"ana":15,"ref":16},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":18,"ana":19,"ref":20},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":22,"ana":23,"ref":24},"marble (white)","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":3},"The epigraphic face is preserved for a width of 12.5 cm, with two lines of Latin letters filling the available field.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":34},"The letters are tall, neatly cut and closely spaced (height c.30mm), and words are separated by simple triangular interpuncts. The letters are lightly serifed. E is tall and narrow, T has a curved cross-bar, rising to the right.",[35,42],{"type":36,"l":37,"from":38,"to":39,"h":40,"unit":41},"letterHeight","Line 1-2","line1","line2","30","mm",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":39,"h":45,"unit":41},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","?",{"_":47,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":49,"precision":50},"Late 1st century CE, or 2nd century CE",51,200,"low",[52,56],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[62],[63,64],37.99907,14.26197,[66,67],37.998047,14.262635,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":71,"role":72,"ref":73},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":75,"type":76},"ME 20226","inventory",{"_":78,"mainLang":79,"languages":80},"Latin","la",[78],"175722",{"n":83,"url":84,"height":85,"width":86,"desc":87,"surfaceType":88},"screen","ISic000768_tiled.tif","3395px","7360px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Soprintendenza di Messina","front",[],[12,91,92,93,94,95,96,97,98],"Epigraphica Halaesina I, 1971","La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano, 1988","Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia, 1989","Alesa Arconidea: ricerche su un'antica città della Sicilia tirrenica, 2006","The Epigraphs, 2008","Le sculture da Alesa, 2009","Spazio pubblico e memoria civica. Le epigrafi dall'agora di Alesa, 2012",", , 2017, Alesa Archonidea: il lapidarium",[100,101,102,103,104,105,106,107,108],"R46KDTZX","UISW82JC","RZSFKACR","EZMBJ6GN","J4XWZPV6","6GFVUASD","BCIMMIKZ","CJISRIUV","MI64NB9L",[110,111,112,14,18,22,113,114,115,116,113,117,118,79],"isic000768","dedication by a sevir to concordia",{"_":11},"halaesa","castel di tusa","italy","sicily","antiquarium e sito archeologico di halaesa","latin","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>Conco]ṛdiae · Aug[ustae\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ethus · sev[ir\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":121,"ptr":122,"ref":124,"title":2,"citation":5},"85-87",{"target":123},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/BCIMMIKZ",{"_":125,"target":125},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001670",{"file":127,"uri":127,"title":128,"status":129,"editionAuthor":12,"type":130,"objectType":131,"material":134,"condition":3,"layoutDesc":135,"handNote":139,"date":151,"places":156,"geo":159,"provenance":53,"provenanceGeo":161,"country":68,"region":69,"settlement":53,"repository":164,"idno":165,"textLang":167,"tmNumber":169,"facsimile":170,"letterHeights":175,"publications":176,"zotero":178,"keywords":180,"html":184,"bibl":185},"ISic000804","Dedication of a statue to Ceres, by Iulius Acilius Hermes, sevir",{"_":11},{"_":14,"ana":15,"ref":16},{"_":132,"ana":133,"ref":20},"statue base","#object.statue_base",{"_":22,"ana":23,"ref":24},{"layout":136},{"p":137,"rs":138,"damage":3},"The Latin text is engraved over two lines (letters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":140,"dimensions":141}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[142,145,148],{"type":36,"l":143,"from":38,"to":38,"h":144,"unit":41},"Line 1","18-25",{"type":36,"l":146,"from":39,"to":39,"h":147,"unit":41},"Line 2","19-23",{"type":43,"l":149,"from":38,"to":39,"h":150,"unit":41},"Interlineation lines 1-2","7-15",{"_":152,"notBefore":153,"notAfter":154,"evidence":155},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,"context",[157,158],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},[160],[63,64],[162,163],37.998037,14.262643,{"_":71,"role":72,"ref":73},{"_":166,"type":76},"ME 20194",{"_":78,"mainLang":79,"languages":168},[78],"175724",{"n":83,"url":171,"height":172,"width":173,"desc":174,"surfaceType":88},"ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina",[],[12,91,92,177,96,97,98],"Statuary, 2008",[100,101,102,179,106,107,108],"EQC3W4UU",[181,182,183,14,132,22,113,114,115,116,113,117,118,79],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":11},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":186,"ptr":187,"ref":188,"title":2,"citation":5},"80-87 fig.7",{"target":123},{"_":125,"target":125}],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
